    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "BEIJING (Reuters) - China’s Foreign Ministry said on Thursday it hoped that Canada can abandon prejudices and provide a level playing field for Chinese companies, after Ottawa blocked a Chinese firm’s purchase of a Canadian construction firm on national security grounds.\nOn Wednesday, Canada said it had rejected the proposed C$1.51 billion ($1.18 billion) takeover of construction firm Aecon Group Inc ( ARE.TO ) by a unit of China Communications Construction Co Ltd ( 601800.SS ).\nReporting by Michael Martina; Writing by Tony Munroe; Editing by Darren Schuettler\n ",
